    <title><anchor xml:id="_Location_Maintenance_Documents"/>Services and Functions Administrative
        Documents</title>
    <para role="Body Text"/>
    <para role="Body Text"><inlinemediaobject>
            <alt>Admin</alt>
            <imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="../images/Admin.png"/>
            </imageobject>
        </inlinemediaobject>
        <emphasis role="bold">&gt;<inlinemediaobject>
                <alt>Services &amp; Functions</alt>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/admin-112.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </inlinemediaobject> &gt; <inlinemediaobject>
                <alt>Services &amp; Functions Links</alt>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/admin-113.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </inlinemediaobject></emphasis></para>
    <para role="Normal"/>
    <section>
        <title><anchor xml:id="_DiscoveryService"/>Discovery Service</title>
        <para role="Body Text"><emphasis role="bold"><inlinemediaobject>
                    <alt>Admin</alt>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/Admin.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject>
                <emphasis role="bold">&gt;<inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>Services &amp; Functions</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="../images/admin-112.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject></emphasis>&gt;<inlinemediaobject>
                    <alt>Discovery Service</alt>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/admin-116.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject></emphasis></para>
        <para role="Body Text">The Discovery Service allows users to search the DocStore database
            and test the RESTful API and SOLR Indexing.<note>
                <para>In order to index and reindex bibliographic, holdings, e-holdings, and item
                    records in Solr, go to <link
                        xlink:href="http://demo.docstore.ole.kuali.org/admin.jsp"
                        >http://demo.docstore.ole.kuali.org/admin.jsp</link> (or <link
                        xlink:href="http://tst.docstore.ole.kuali.org/admin.jsp"
                        >http://tst.docstore.ole.kuali.org/admin.jsp</link> if you are in the tst
                    environment).</para>
                <para>Click the <emphasis role="bold">Start</emphasis> button. </para>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Show Status</emphasis> button to see the status. </para>
                <para>Indexing is complete when you see the "Index End Time"</para>
            </note></para>
        <para/>
        <para role="Normal">
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <alt>Discovery Service Display</alt>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/admin-117.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
        </para>
        <para role="Normal">The Grey tabs are explained here:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Summary</emphasis> tab: Shows the summary of record
                    count for each category, type and format</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Test RESTful API</emphasis> tab: Allows users to test
                    the Get and Delete methods of the REST web services.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Sample SOLR queries</emphasis> tab: Displays some sample
                    queries' data for SOLR.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Admin Pages</emphasis> tab: Contains administrative
                    links for SOLR.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para>Click the <emphasis role="bold">OLE</emphasis> tab to return to OLE's main
            portal.</para>
        <para role="Normal">
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <alt>Document Store Tabs: Click OLE to return to the regular OLE Interface</alt>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-30a.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
        </para>
        <section>
            <title><anchor xml:id="_DocStoreSearch"/>Document Store Search</title>
            <section>
                <title>Performing a Document Store Search</title>
                <para role="Normal">From the <emphasis role="bold">Search</emphasis> tab,
                    bibliographic data in the DocStore can be searched in a variety of ways. Select
                    options from the drop down menus and enter information to refine the
                    search.</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Search Screen</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-12.png"
                                    width="100%"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="TableHeading"><emphasis role="bold">Advance Search Field
                        Definitions</emphasis></para>
                <informaltable frame="top">
                    <tgroup cols="2">
                        <colspec colname="col1" colnum="1"/>
                        <colspec colname="col2" colnum="2"/>
                        <tbody>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">Title </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">Description </para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">Document Category </para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">General category of documents being
                                        searched.  </para>
                                    <note>
                                        <para role="Table Cells"> Work is the only valid category in
                                            1.5</para>
                                    </note>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">Document Type</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">Type of documents associated with a
                                        category.</para>
                                    <para role="Table Cells">For the category <emphasis role="bold"
                                            >Work</emphasis>, these include bibliographic, licenses,
                                        Instances, items, etc.</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">Document Format</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">Limits searches to a specific data
                                        format (i.e., MARC, Dublin Core). Defaults to <emphasis
                                            role="bold">ALL</emphasis>.</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                            <row>
                                <entry colname="col1" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">Sort By</para>
                                </entry>
                                <entry colname="col2" colsep="1" rowsep="1" valign="top">
                                    <para role="Table Cells">Sorts the records by title, author,
                                        publication date, and relevance</para>
                                </entry>
                            </row>
                        </tbody>
                    </tgroup>
                </informaltable>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">Five search lines are provided in the Document Store Discovery
                    Layer.  Standard Boolean operators (AND, OR, NOT) can be chosen to combine the
                    search terms.  Truncation is not automatic in OLE 1.0; the truncation symbol is
                    an asterisk.  An asterisk can also be used as a wildcard character within a
                    word. </para>
                <note>
                    <para role="Normal"><emphasis> Known bug:</emphasis> Special characters such as
                        ‘&amp;’ and ‘:’ are not recognized when searching.</para>
                </note>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">A default sort for the result set can be specified from either
                    the search or the results screen. After all search and sort parameters are
                    entered, click <inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>Search</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-15.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject>.</para>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Sample Search Results</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-16.png"
                                    width="100%"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">A short selection of fields from the bibliographic data is
                    displayed for each title.</para>
                <para role="Normal">To refine your search, you can use the <emphasis role="bold"
                        >facets</emphasis> on the left-hand side of the results screen:</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Sample Facet Menu</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-17.png"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">Clicking on these returns a smaller, more limited search result
                    set.  Clicking on more than one facet reduces the result set even further.  The
                    facets being used for limiting results are shown at the top of the results
                    index:</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Sample Facets at the top of the Search Results
                                Screen</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-18.png"
                                    width="100%"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal">To remove a limit, click on the red <emphasis role="bold"
                        >[x]</emphasis> next to it.</para>
                <para role="Normal">The search results are then re-displayed with that limit
                    removed.</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">If you need to see more titles on a screen, each entry can be
                    collapsed to show only its titles.  All entries can be collapsed at once by
                    using the <emphasis role="bold">Collapse All</emphasis> link in the upper
                    right:</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Sample Search Results Collapsed</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-19.jpg"
                                    width="100%"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">To view more results you may slide or click on the search bar,
                    type in a page number, or hover your mouse near the left of the <emphasis
                        role="bold">Selected page </emphasis>field to use the up/down arrows. You
                    will then need to click <emphasis role="bold">Go to page</emphasis>.</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Navigation Features</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-20.jpg"
                                    width="100%"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">OLE is designed to search data in a variety of formats.  OLE
                    contains bibliographic data in MARC and Dublin Core formats, both stored in XML.
                     The record format is shown at the bottom of the bibliographic
                    information.</para>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Sample Record</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-20a.png"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal">Just below the bibliographic details for each title are links to
                    the XML versions.  Click <inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>View</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-20b.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> to open an XML version of the record in a new window or
                    browser tab:</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>Sample XML Bibliographic Record</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-21.png"
                                    width="100%"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">Click <inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>Edit</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-20c.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> to open the Bibliographic Editor.</para>
                <note>
                    <para role="Normal"> For more information about the bibliographic editor, see
                        the <link xlink:href="../../../webhelp/CG/content/ch01s02.html">Editors</link> section of
                        the <link xlink:href="../../../webhelp/CG/content/pr01.html"><emphasis role="italic">Guide to the
                                Describe and Manage Module</emphasis></link>.</para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para role="Normal"> Note: The View and Edit buttons will most likely change in
                        future releases.</para>
                </note>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">At any time, you may choose to revise your search or start a new
                    search. These options are located at the top left side of the results
                    screen.</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>Revise Search/New Search Buttons above Facets Menu</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-24.png"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para>Click the <emphasis role="bold">OLE</emphasis> tab to return to OLE's main
                    portal.</para>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Tabs</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-30a.png"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
            </section>
            <section>
                <title>OLE Instance Searching</title>
                <para role="Normal">Some bibliographic search results may include link(s) to one to
                    many Instance (with Holding) and Item records, for those created during
                    acquisitions or as part of OLE sample data:</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Sample Records with Instance and Item Records</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-26.png"
                                    width="100%"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">You may select the <emphasis role="bold">call number</emphasis>
                    link to see the Instance metadata, or link from it to further Holding or Item(s)
                    data. There is limited data in the Item records that have been added to the
                    Document Store. To return to the Bibliographic description, click the <emphasis
                        role="bold">Title</emphasis> link.</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">To return to your search results, use your browser's
                    navigation.</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">At present, users only have the <emphasis role="bold">Search
                        Field</emphasis> option "source" available when searching Instance
                    documents, but can further search Holdings data like below:</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Search Screen with Document Type Instance Holding
                                Selected</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-29.png"
                                    width="100%"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal"> </para>
                <para role="Normal">Or further, test searching on Item data. </para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">
                    <screenshot>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <alt>DocStore Search Screen with Document Type Instance Item
                                Selected</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-30.png"
                                    width="100%"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </screenshot>
                </para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal">Facets for Holdings and Item data (such as location, call number
                    sorting, etc.) will be designed and released in the future.</para>
                <para role="Normal"/>
                <para role="Normal"><emphasis role="bold">Notes and Tips on Bib, Instance and Item
                        searching</emphasis></para>
                <itemizedlist mark="disc" spacing="normal">
                    <listitem>
                        <para role="List Paragraph">Breadcrumbs are planned for a later release, for
                            now you can navigate through the DocStore but will want to make note of
                            where you have been if you want to return to the same record.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para role="List Paragraph">If you use multiple words in your search, only
                            one gets highlighted in the search results, and it’s the first word that
                            appears in the document (not the first word in your list of search
                            terms).</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para role="List Paragraph">If you search for a word in plural form, OLE
                            will show results for the singular form as well.</para>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>Click the <emphasis role="bold">OLE</emphasis> tab to return to OLE's
                            main portal.</para>
                        <para role="Normal">
                            <screenshot>
                                <mediaobject>
                                    <alt>DocStore tabs: Click OLE to return to the Regular OLE
                                        Interface</alt>
                                    <imageobject>
                                        <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-30a.png"/>
                                    </imageobject>
                                </mediaobject>
                            </screenshot>
                        </para>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist>
                <para role="List Paragraph"/>
                <para role="Normal">Click <inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>View</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="../images/DescribeNoTitlePage-31.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject> to see Instance, Holdings or Items in their raw XML form.
                    OLE will generate new Instance/Holding/Item documents during the Import or Load
                    process or during Requisition-to-Purchase Order creation. You may also create
                    and edit Instances through the Instance Editor.</para>
                <note>
                    <para role="Normal"> For more information about the Instance editor, see the
                        <link xlink:href="../../../webhelp/CG/content/ch01s03.html">Instance
                            Editor</link> section of the <link xlink:href="../../../webhelp/CG/content/pr01.html"
                                ><emphasis role="italic">Guide to the Describe and Manage
                                Module</emphasis></link>.</para>
                </note>
                <para role="Normal"/>
            </section>
        </section>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title><anchor xml:id="_DocStoreService"/>DocStore Service</title>
        <para role="Body Text"><emphasis role="bold"><inlinemediaobject>
                    <alt>Admin</alt>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/Admin.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject>
                <emphasis role="bold">&gt;<inlinemediaobject>
                        <alt>Services &amp; Functions</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="../images/admin-112.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </inlinemediaobject></emphasis>&gt;<inlinemediaobject>
                    <alt>Docstore Service</alt>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/admin-114.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject></emphasis></para>
        <para>The functionality of Docstore is mostly used by other processes like OLE.  However,
            for demonstration and testing docstore, this screen is provided with different functions
            of docstore and information about docstore.</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Ingest</emphasis>: Allows storing of documents in the
                    document store. The input should be a Request XML with a standard schema and
                    returns the Response XML with a list of ingested UUIDs.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Check-in</emphasis>:  Check-in functionality allows to
                    modify the content and metadata (additional attributes) of a document identified
                    by its UUID (Universally Unique Identifier).</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Check-out</emphasis>:  This operation retrieves the
                    content of a document given its UUID.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para><emphasis role="bold">Batch Delete</emphasis>:  Delete records from
                    DocumentStore based on UUIDs.</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title><anchor xml:id="_Patron_Merge"/>Patron Merge</title>
        <para role="Body Text"><inlinemediaobject>
                <alt>Admin</alt>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="../images/Admin.png"/>
                </imageobject>
            </inlinemediaobject>
            <emphasis role="bold">&gt;<inlinemediaobject>
                    <alt>Services &amp; Functions</alt>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/admin-112.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject></emphasis><emphasis role="bold"> &gt;<inlinemediaobject>
                    <alt>Patron Merge</alt>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/DeliverNoTitlePage-161.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject> &gt; <inlinemediaobject>
                    <alt>Patron Merge</alt>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="../images/DeliverNoTitlePage-162.png"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </inlinemediaobject>
            </emphasis></para>
        <para>Patron Merge is used to merge two or more patron records online. Patron Merge allows a
            duly-authorized operator to display all records to be merged. Any records of any kind
            linked to a duplicate record(s) will be relinked to the survivor record.</para>
        <section>
            <title role="Heading 4circ">Process Overview</title>
            <para role="Body Text">
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <alt>Patron Merge Interface</alt>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="../images/DeliverNoTitlePage-163.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </para>
            <orderedlist numeration="arabic" spacing="normal">
                <listitem>
                    <para role="List Paragraph">From the <emphasis role="bold">Patron
                            Merge</emphasis> screen, search for the patron by <emphasis role="bold"
                            >first name</emphasis>, <emphasis role="bold">last name</emphasis>
                        and/or <emphasis role="bold">patron type</emphasis></para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para role="List Paragraph">Click <inlinemediaobject>
                            <alt>Search</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DeliverNoTitlePage-164.png"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </inlinemediaobject></para>
                    <para role="Normal">A list of persons will appear below the search.</para>
                    <para role="Normal"/>
                    <para role="Normal">
                        <screenshot>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <alt>Patron Merge with Sample Patrons Displayed</alt>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="../images/DeliverNoTitlePage-165.png"
                                        width="100%"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </screenshot>
                    </para>
                    <para role="Normal"/>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para role="List Paragraph">Select the <emphasis role="bold"
                        >Survivor</emphasis>, the record that will remain.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para role="List Paragraph">Select the <emphasis role="bold">Duplicate
                            Patron(s)</emphasis> that will be added to the survivor record.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para role="List Paragraph">Click <inlinemediaobject>
                            <alt>Merge</alt>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="../images/DeliverNoTitlePage-166.png"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </inlinemediaobject>.</para>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </section>
    </section>
</chapter>
